On April 2, 2009, the White House released a statement by the President regarding the House passage of the FY10 budget. The statement highlighted the budget's focus on rebuilding the economy, with priorities including an energy plan to reduce dependence on foreign oil, an education system that prepares children for the 21st-century economy, and healthcare reform to address rising costs. The President also emphasized the need to make hard choices and challenge old ways of doing business in order to cut the budget deficit in half within four years. The statement concluded with a call to go through the budget line-by-line to find additional savings.